	<h2 id="key-takeaways" class="vf-u-margin--0 vf-u-padding__top--400 vf-u-padding__bottom--600">Key Takeaways</h2>
	<p>Graceful Degradation is an essential resilience strategy that ensures systems remain functional even when parts fail. Rather than preventing all failures, it focuses on controlling their impact.</p>
	<p>Key outcomes include:</p>
	<ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
		<li class="vf-list__item">Improved reliability</li>
		<li class="vf-list__item">Broader accessibility</li>
		<li class="vf-list__item">Better user experience during disruptions</li>
		<li class="vf-list__item">Reduced system downtime</li>
		<li class="vf-list__item">Greater resilience in distributed systems</li>
	</ul>

